00:00:00.940 --> 00:00:04.700
We now begin the catalog and for each of the particular principles we're going

00:00:04.700 --> 00:00:09.380
to give the principle's name, its author, a definition and the implications of

00:00:09.380 --> 00:00:13.200
its, of its use. But, before we start, please remember these are guidelines and

00:00:13.200 --> 00:00:16.120
not hard-and-fast rules and in any given situation you have to

00:00:16.120 --> 00:00:20.790
decide which principle may or may not be appropriate and

00:00:20.790 --> 00:00:24.920
whether just how you're going to apply it. The guidelines presented in

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:27.990
this catalog are taken from the writings of many different authors and

00:00:27.990 --> 00:00:31.360
more details on the sources are found on the class resources page.

